{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e910185d-7007-41b6-9f06-5fbc8dd8c08c","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` — it re-runs tests automatically whenever you save a file:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThe `--filter` flag restricts it to just your failing test. Every time you save `InventoryServiceTests.cs`, it will rebuild and re-run automatically.\n\n**The bug:** `RemoveStock` never validates that enough stock exists — it just subtracts. You need to add a guard that throws `InvalidOperationException` when `quantity > available`. Fix `RemoveStock` to something like:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply the fix and verify it passes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"664ca114-1179-4d16-94e6-3865483ec838","outputTokens":232,"requestId":"67C7:14F926:2C05AFE:30B20D3:69FD3FEC"},"id":"5b542cb1-bbd9-454b-a57c-e2526d6a87e0","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:44:18.611Z","parentId":"be54d6f2-3b41-4bef-9e67-32a15c8ff53f"}
